Yen Falls, Paring Yesterday's Gains, on Speculation Global Recovery Intact

-- B y   R o n n i e   H a r u i
-- 
2011-04-08T01:00:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/yen-falls-paring-yesterday-s-gains-on-speculation-global-recovery-intact.html
The yen declined, paring gains from
yesterday, as signs the global economic recovery remains intact
curbed demand for  Japan ’s currency as a refuge.  The yen weakened to 85.14 to the dollar as of 9:58 a.m. in
 Tokyo  from 84.91 in  New York  yesterday, when it advanced 0.7
percent. Japan’s currency slipped to 121.86 per  euro  from
121.49.  To contact the reporter on this story:
